ich-honors-100-years-of-route-66-180988868/</guid></item><item><title>杀虫剂能吸引蚊子吗？实验室昆虫发现避蚊胺的气味会让它们吃到美味佳肴</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-bug-spray-attract-mosquitoes-lab-insects-learned-that-the-smell-of-deet-would-lead-them-to-a-tasty-treat-180988866/</link><description>研究人员不知道这些发现如何与现实世界的环境重叠。但这一发现表明，当驱虫剂失效时，我们最容易受到伤害，这意味着我们应该定期重新使用它</description><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-bug-spray-attract-mosquitoes-lab-insects-learned-that-the-smell-of-deet-would-lead-them-to-a-tasty-treat-180988866/</guid></item><item><title>韩国和法国文化将在首尔新现代和当代艺术博物馆交汇</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/korean-and-french-culture-are-set-to-rendezvous-at-a-new-museum-in-seoul-for-modern-and-contemporary-art-180988864/</link><description>蓬皮杜韩华艺术中心是日益壮大的全球艺术博物馆网络的最新成员，将首次举办欧洲立体主义和韩国艺术展览</description><pubDate>Sun, 31 May 2026 19:01:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/korean-and-french-culture-are-set-to-rendezvous-at-a-new-museum-in-seoul-for-modern-and-contemporary-art-180988864/</guid></item><item><title>四只稀有的关岛翠鸟雏鸟在弗吉尼亚州的设施中孵化，为少量已灭绝的野生鸟类增添了“极其宝贵”的资源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/four-rare-guam-kingfisher-chicks-hatch-at-virginia-facility-making-an-incredibly-valuable-addition-to-the-small-population-of-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-180988863/</link><description>该物种也被称为“sihek”，在其故乡关岛被消灭，并被圈养存活。 2024年，环保主义者在巴尔米拉环礁放生了一些鸟类，迄今为止它们一直繁衍生息</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 21:00:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/four-rare-guam-kingfisher-chicks-hatch-at-virginia-facility-making-an-incredibly-valuable-addition-to-the-small-population-of-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-180988863/</guid></item><item><title>这些具有 600 年历史的中国手术器械涂有早期局部麻醉剂——从有毒植物中精心提取</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-600-year-old-chinese-surgical-instruments-are-coated-in-an-early-local-anestheticcarefully-extracted-from-a-poisonous-plant-180988865/</link><description>研究人员表示，在手术过程中，麻醉剂溅到了铁剪刀和镊子上。它们是在明代医生墓中发现的</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 20:15:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-600-year-old-chinese-surgical-instruments-are-coated-in-an-early-local-anestheticcarefully-extracted-from-a-poisonous-plant-180988865/</guid></item><item><title>亚洲象 Happy 于布朗克斯动物园去世，享年 55 岁</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/happy-an-asian-elephant-who-demonstrated-that-her-species-might-be-self-aware-dies-at-55-at-the-bronx-zoo-180988861/</link><description>大约 20 年前的研究报告显示，哈皮似乎在镜子里认出了自己。她后来成为一场失败诉讼的对象，该诉讼声称大象应该享有某些基本人权</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 18:23:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/happy-an-asian-elephant-who-demonstrated-that-her-species-might-be-self-aware-dies-at-55-at-the-bronx-zoo-180988861/</guid></item><item><title>艺术家利用彩色狗粮，将《蒙娜丽莎》、《尖叫》和《吻》变成人类最好的朋友可以欣赏的博物馆杰作</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/using-colorful-kibble-artists-turn-mona-lisa-the-scream-and-the-kiss-into-museum-masterpieces-that-mans-best-friend-can-appreciate-180988860/</link><description>来自新泽西州的姐妹们花了两个月的时间重新创作著名的艺术品，同时确保她们的狗不会进入可食用的艺术用品</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 18:16:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/using-colorful-kibble-artists-turn-mona-lisa-the-scream-and-the-kiss-into-museum-masterpieces-that-mans-best-friend-can-appreciate-180988860/</guid></item><item><title>希尔玛·阿夫·克林特 (Hilma af Klint) 是一位相信超凡脱俗的灵魂告诉她要画什么的神秘主义者。现在，她被认为是历史上第一位抽象艺术家之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-hilma-af-klint-the-occultist-who-believed-otherworldly-spirits-told-her-what-to-paint-now-shes-considered-one-of-historys-first-abstract-artists-180988859/</link><description>这位瑞典画家早在 1906 年就创作了大胆、充满活力的作品，比瓦西里·康定斯基等同时代人早了几年。法国举办的新展览庆祝她的“圣殿绘画”系列</description><